<P>
   PUTIN-EDITORIAL _ Vladimir Putin campaigned for Russia's
presidency without revealing much about his personality or program.
What little outsiders know about him is mostly off-putting. Just
the same, he is a fact of life, and the U.S. must work with him on
initiatives with potential mutual benefit such as arms reduction
and economic development. (Atlanta Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   KELSO-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ No one can accuse management at
the Texas Natural Resource Conservation Commission of being overly
warm and fuzzy. When the state agency wanted to show its workers
what could happen to them if they parked in the wrong spot at work,
they displayed a state van in a company parking lot with a vehicle
restraint device attached to the left front wheel. (Kelso, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   REAL-LIFE _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ It started with just one
cigarette. After almost two years, I started smoking again. (Minor,
Palm Beach Post)
</P>
