   FOOD-RECIPESWAP _ A weekly recipe exchange column. This week:
Peanut Butter frosting. (Langhenry, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-CYBERSPICE _ A weekly column looking at the plethora of
recipes on the Internet. This week: recipes for pets. (Parham,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   COXNET-WRESTLING PAGE
</P>
<P>
   Keying to the Monday wrestling events, It's good for publication
any day through Sunday. Here are the elements on the page, which
are also moving on the entertainment wire:
</P>
<P>
   COXNET-WRESTLING 0330:
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-TAGTEAMS _ In biblical times, anyone searching for an
expert on pairs would probably look up Noah. In pro wrestling, the
most likely source of expertise on twosomes is Captain Lou Albano.
And with good reason. Albano has managed 19 tag-team champions,
including several duos that held the titles more than once. And he
even wore a tag-team championship belt around his own ample waist
at one time. ``I looked for guys that were a good size and could
work together in the ring,'' said Albano, now a 67-year-old
grandfather (he has 13 grandchildren to go with his four grown
children). A rundown of Albano's list of champions reveals that
``good size'' might be putting it mildly. (Braun, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   w/WRESTLING-KOWALSKI _ Walter Kowalski wasn't always known as
``Killer.'' He actually started his career as Tarzan Kowalski, and
was a babyface. But when the fans started booing him, he became a
heel. (Braun, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE _ News, notes, gossip from the wrestling
industry. (Allen, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-SENSE _ Video pick of the week: ``The Sixth Sense.''
Grade: B+ (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-MINIS _ Coming soon: ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom
Menace,'' ``The Mesenger: The Story of Joan of Arc,'' ``For Love of
the Game.'' (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-RINGEL _ Eleanor Ringel Gillespie notes that the Oscar
awards has '60s reminders and recommends some videos that would be
an at-home '60s Festival, including ``Midnight Cowboy,'' ``Alfie''
and ``The Apartment.'' (Ringel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-TAMAR _ ``Tamar,'' debut album by Toni Braxton's sister.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-MINIS _ NYC rapper Drag-On's ``Drag-On,'' ``Jesus''
soundtrack, and ``Gung Ho'' by Patti Smith. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-COUNTRY _ ``Real Live Woman,'' new album by Trisha
Yearwood. (Longino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
