<P>
   THAILAND-POLITICS (Bangkok) _ Thailand's tough and powerful
interior minister resigned Wednesday after a newly formed
anti-corruption agency charged hat he had concealed his assets by
fabricating a million-dollar loan. By Seth Mydans.
</P>
<P>
   (An early version of this story will move by 1 p.m. EST)
</P>
<P>
   TAIWAN-POLITICS (Beijing) _ In a surprise announcement, Taiwan's
president-elect, Chen Shui-bian, said Wednesday that the outgoing
Nationalist Party defense minister would be prime minister of his
new government that takes office May 20. By Erik Eckholm.
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-CAVES (Jerusalem) _ Palestinian shepherds and farmers who
were evicted from the caves where they had lived in an area of the
Hebron hills can return to their caves, an Israeli court rules. By
Joel Greenberg.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-ISHIHARA (Tokyo) _ If any politician was ever going to try
to break the central government's hold over almost every aspect of
Japanese life, it seemed most likely to be the ever-crusading
shoot-from-the-lip governor of Tokyo, Shintaro Ishihara. By Howard
W. French.
</P>
