<HEADER>
A1143 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r d BC-DOUGH2-RECIPES-LADN &LR;      03-29 0759
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DOUGH2-RECIPES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LEMON DANISH
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: Fact box below) 
Our rating: x stars 
By NATALIE HAUGHTON 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   LEMON DANISH ROLLS &QL; 
2 (1-pound) loaves frozen white bread dough, thawed &QL; 
1/4 cup melted butter OR margarine &QL; 
1 (3-ounce) package regular (NOT INSTANT) lemon pie filling mix,
prepared as directed, or 2 cups favorite prepared lemon filling &QL; 
Lemon Glaze
</P>
<P>
   Divide each loaf of dough into 8 pieces (total of 16 pieces for
the 2 loaves). Gently roll each piece into a ball; flatten
slightly. Place on greased baking sheets about 2 inches apart.
Brush with melted butter. Let rise 1 to 2 hours in a warm place,
until double in size.
</P>
<P>
   Make indentations about 1-inch wide in center of each ball,
pressing to bottom. Fill each with 2 tablespoons lemon filling.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 350-degree oven 10 to 12 minutes or until
rolls just begin to turn golden brown. Remove from oven and brush
with melted butter. Remove from baking sheets and cool on wire
racks. When cool, drizzle with Lemon Glaze. Makes 16 rolls.
</P>
<P>
   LEMON GLAZE: Mix 2 cups powdered sugar with 2 tablespoons lemon
juice and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
ORANGE BUBBLE LOAF &QL; 
1 1/2 loaves (1 1/2 pounds total) frozen bread dough, white OR
honey wheat OR 1 (27-ounce) package white rolls OR 1 (25-ounce)
package Parkerhouse rolls &QL; 
1 1/2 cups granulated sugar &QL; 
2 teaspoons grated orange peel &QL; 
6 tablespoons butter OR margarine, melted
</P>
<P>
   Let dough thaw. If using bread dough, divide whole loaf into 16
pieces and half loaf into 8 pieces, for a total of 24 pieces. If
using rolls, do not divide.
</P>
<P>
   Shape each roll or piece of dough into a ball. Mix sugar and
orange peel. Dip each ball in butter, then into sugar-orange
mixture.
</P>
<P>
   Arrange balls of dough in a greased bundt cake or tube pan. Let
rise in a warm area until dough is double in size or rises to top
of pan.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in a preheated 350-degree oven 40 minutes. If bread is
browning too quickly, cover with foil. To test for doneness, gently
tap baked loaf on top with tip of a knife _ if it sounds hollow, it
should be done.
</P>
<P>
   Remove bread from oven and invert pan on a large plate. Remove
pan and allow bread to cool. Garnish top with mandarin oranges,
drained, if desired. Makes 1 loaf. &QL; 
ARTICHOKE CALZONE &QL; 
1 (1-pound) loaf frozen white bread dough, thawed &QL; 
2 tablespoons olive oil &QL; 
1 teaspoon (OR more) garlic powder &QL; 
4 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese &QL; 
1 (6-ounce) jar marinated artichoke hearts, drained &QL; 
1 (2.25-ounce) can sliced ripe olives, drained &QL; 
1 (4-ounce) can sliced mushrooms, drained &QL; 
1/2 cup dried tomatoes, softened and thinly sliced according to
package directions OR 1/2 cup sliced dried tomatoes packed in oil,
drained &QL; 
1 cup shredded provolone OR mozzarella cheese &QL; 
Egg wash (1 egg yolk mixed with 1 tablespoon water) OR melted
butter
</P>
<P>
   Divide dough into 4 equal portions. On a lightly floured
surface, roll or pat each piece into a circle 6 inches in diameter.
Brush each circle with olive oil and sprinkle generously with
garlic powder. Top with grated Parmesan.
</P>
<P>
   Mix together artichokes, olives, mushrooms and tomatoes. Divide
mixture between 4 dough rounds and spread over half of each dough
circle. Top artichoke mixture with provolone cheese. Fold dough
over filling and seal by pinching edges tightly. Brush dough with
egg wash or melted butter.
</P>
<P>
   Bake in preheated 375-degree oven 20 to 30 minutes or until well
browned. Remove from oven to cool on wire rack. Serve warm. Makes 4
calzones. &QL; 
ONION BIALYS &QL; 
1 (1-pound) loaf frozen white bread dough, thawed &QL; 
2 tablespoons butter, melted OR vegetable oil &QL; 
1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped &QL; 
1 tablespoon poppy seeds
</P>
<P>
   Grease a baking sheet; lightly dust with cornmeal. Divide thawed
loaf into 6 equal pieces. Shape each piece into a round
approximately 4 to 5 inches in diameter, then flatten center to
create a rim around edge.
</P>
<P>
   Place bialys on baking sheet 3 inches apart. Prick flattened
centers of dough rounds with a fork. Set aside. Let rise until
almost double in size.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile make topping. In a medium skillet, heat butter. Sautee
onions until soft. Add poppy seeds. Let cool. Spoon 1 to 2
tablespoons onion filling in center of each bialy.
</P>
<P>
   Fill an 8-inch square baking pan 1/4 full of ice water. Place in
oven on bottom rack. Place tray of risen bialys in oven on center
rack. Bake in preheated 400-degree oven 10 minutes or until golden
brown. Remove from oven and remove bialys to wire rack to cool.
Makes 6 servings. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
