Inc. and Medtronic Inc. By Claudia H. Deutsch.
</P>
<P>
   PHILIPS-CZECH (Prague) _ Royal Philips Electronics, the Dutch
consumer electronics giant, will build one of the world's largest
television tube factories in the Czech Republic, reflecting growing
demand in Eastern Europe. The project, which could cost more than
$500 million, is the biggest single foreign investment in the Czech
Republic and will employ more than 3,000 people in one of its most
economically depressed regions. By Ladka Bauerrova.
</P>
<P>
   EMBRAER-EARNINGS (Sao Paulo) _ Empresa Brasileira de
Aeronautica, one of Brazil's most successful companies, says
earnings more than quadrupled in the fourth quarter because of
strong demand for its jetliners. The results at Embraer, as it is
known for short, greatly exceeded expectations. By Simon Romero.
</P>
<P>
   ECONSCENE (Undated) _ The weekly Economic Scene column.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; COMMENTARY &LR;  (``k'' code)
</P>
<P>
   Bob Herbert's ``In America'' and William Safire's ``Essay.''
</P>
<P>
