media know.''
</P>
<P>
   She added that the families and doctors hoped the surgery could
be rescheduled soon, but she provided no specific timetable.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Has Chelsea Clinton taken a leave of absence from Stanford?
I've seen pictures of her in Washington, and taking trips and
making appearances with her parents. A newspaper photo showed her
in India recently with the presidential party.
</P>
<P>
   A: The first daughter is still enrolled at Stanford University,
and the first lady's press office confirmed that Wednesday. She's
on spring break, a spokeswoman said, which allowed her time to join
the current overseas trip.
</P>
<P>
   Q: It was reported several years ago that a U-boat that was sunk
in 1945 was found off the Danish coast. It was supposed to be
recovered and its contents examined. What became of that?
</P>
<P>
   A: The 255-foot German submarine, which was on its way to the
North Sea and ultimately to Japan, was sunk by a British bomber on
May 5, 1945. It was brought to the surface 15 miles off the small
