<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RECIPES-BUNDY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PROTEIN-PACKED LENTILS DELICIOUS DURING LENT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BEVERLY BUNDY 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   R. Nagy of North Richland Hills, Texas, is looking for a recipe
for a lentil soup and also want to know where to buy
``light-colored'' lentils.
</P>
<P>
   Lentils, after soybeans, have the highest protein count of all
vegetables _ hence their popularity with vegetarians. And they come
in many shades, from the green lentils that are so chic (and
relatively expensive) in France to yellow, brown, pink and gray
lentils, which are a mainstay in the Middle East and India. Indian
markets are a great source for lentils of all colors, as are
health-food and other ``alternative'' groceries.
</P>
<P>
   Lentils are often eaten during Lent, when the observant are
avoiding meat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   SPINACH AND LENTIL SOUP
</P>
<P>
   Serves 5
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   1 cup chopped onions
</P>
<P>
   3 cloves garlic, minced
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon ground cumin
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon ground coriander
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon paprika
</P>
<P>
   10 ounces fresh spinach, washed and trimmed of tough stems
</P>
<P>
   1/8 teaspoon Tabasco sauce
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon dried oregano
</P>
<P>
   1 cup lentils, rinsed and picked through
</P>
<P>
   7 cups reduced-sodium, defatted chicken broth
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon kosher salt, or more to taste
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon freshly ground pepper, or more to taste
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   2 tablespoons tomato paste
</P>
<P>
   Heat oil in soup pot over low heat. Saute onions and garlic in
oil until onions are soft and golden. Add cumin, coriander and
paprika. Stir and cook until aromas intensify.
</P>
<P>
   Coarsely chop spinach. Add to onion/garlic /spice mixture and
cook it until it wilts.
</P>
<P>
   Add Tabasco, oregano, lentils and broth. Bring soup to boil,
then immediately reduce to simmer. Cook, covered, for about 50
minutes, until lentils become very soft.
</P>
<P>
   Stir in salt, pepper, lemon juice and tomato paste. Simmer for
10 minutes more. Add more salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 157 calories, 3 grams fat, 22
grams carbohydrates, 13 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 532
milligrams sodium, 17 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``1,000 Lowfat Recipes'' by Terry Blonder Golson (Macmillan,
$29.95)
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   EGYPTIAN RED LENTIL SOUP
</P>
<P>
   Serves 6-8
</P>
<P>
   5 cups water
</P>
<P>
   1 cup dried red lentils
</P>
<P>
   2 cups chopped onions
</P>
<P>
   2 cups chopped potatoes
</P>
<P>
   8 large garlic cloves, peeled and left whole
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon canola or other vegetable oil
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons ground cumin
</P>
<P>
   1/2 teaspoon turmeric
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   1/3 cup chopped fresh cilantro
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons fresh lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   Salt and ground black pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   Combine water, lentils, onions, potatoes and garlic in soup pot.
Cover and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until everything is
tender, 15-20 minutes. Remove from heat.
</P>
<P>
   In small saucepan on low heat, warm oil until it is hot but not
smoking. Add cumin, turmeric and salt; cook, stirring constantly,
for 2-3 minutes, until cumin is fragrant. Take care not to scorch
spices. Set aside for about a minute, or the oil may splatter when
added to the soup. Stir slightly cooled spices into soup and add
cilantro.
</P>
<P>
   Working in small batches, puree soup in blender until smooth.
Add lemon juice. Return soup to pot and reheat gently. Add salt and
pepper to taste.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 149 calories, 2 grams fat, 26
grams carbohydrates, 8 grams protein, 0 cholesterol, 303 milligrams
sodium, 13 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _ ``Moosewood Restaurant Daily Special'' by the Moosewood
Collective (Potter, $24)
</P>
<P>
   (Beverly Bundy is food editor for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Send recipes and requests to Beverly Bundy, Fort Worth
Star-Telegram, Box 1870, Fort Worth, Texas 76101. Or E-mail to
bbundy(at)star-telegram.com. Include a daytime phone number.
Responses to requests will be made only through this column. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
