<SLUG> BC-SMALLTOWN-EATS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MMMMMMMM, GOOD; OUT-OF-THE-WAY DINING DELIGHT
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Resending to eliminate extraneous line at end) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BUD KENNEDY 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Greenwood is a mighty small Texas town.
</P>
<P>
   It's so small, it barely has two players for a domino game.
</P>
<P>
   It has the Greenwood Grocery, though, and a narrow country road
leading to thick cheeseburgers and home-baked meringue and fruit
pies that are stirring talk across four counties.
</P>
<P>
   Greenwood, population 76, is in the ultimate North Texas middle
of nowhere. It's between Slidell and Rosston, near the Denton
County-Wise County line. Take Interstate 35 north to Sanger and
turn west, or take U.S. 287 north to Decatur and turn east. Look
for Texas 51 and then for Farm Road 1204.
</P>
<P>
   Cook-owner Virginia Mann and her husband, Carlton, both
Bridgeport school employees, took over the 60-year-old Greenwood
Grocery Jan. 1. They quickly beefed up breakfasts and lunches, and
word of the fresh-ground cheeseburgers spread quickly across area
farms and horse pastures.
</P>
<P>
   Cooking runs in the family, Virginia Mann said proudly: ``I'm a
Pinkerton'' _ a Decatur grocery family known for homemade Pinkerton
Peanut Patties.
</P>
<P>
   Somebody at the Denton County Courthouse told me about great
pies in Greenwood. On the Saturday when I finally found the town,
the Greenwood Grocery pies included chocolate meringue, coconut
meringue and buttermilk. Another recent Saturday offering included
pineapple cream.
</P>
<P>
   Weekday lunch specials include soft tacos and sandwiches.
Cheeseburgers and pie are great any day. The Greenwood Grocery is
open from 7:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. weekdays, until 6 p.m. Saturdays.
It's at 102 Main St. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
