<P>
   SCOTUS-NUDE (Washington) _ The Supreme Court ruled Wednesday
that cities and states may ban nude dancing as a way of combatting
crime and other ``negative secondary effects'' associated with
establishments that offer this kind of entertainment. In its 6-3
vote upholding an Erie, Pa. ordinance that requires exotic dancers
to wear at least pasties and a G-string, the court's fractured
majority did not explain how that requirement would reduce the
crime, prostitution, sexual assaults or other problems associated
with places where dancers appear fully nude. By Linda Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   FLAG-DESECRATE (Washington) _ The Senate considers a
constitutional amendment banning flag desecration. The House last
year approved the amendment by more than the needed two-thirds
majority, but the Senate outcome is expected to be similar to a
1995 attempt that fell three votes shy. (Summary from wires) By
Lizette Alvarez.
