   BELLSOUTH-STOCK _ ATLANTA _ BellSouth Corp has filed with the
Securities and Exchange Commission plans to create a tracking stock
for all its Latin American businesses. Coming as AT&AMP;T prepares its
huge wireless tracker _ and as BellSouth stock languishes _ the
BellSouth plan is aimed at getting investors to see the 10-country,
Latin America unit's solid growth and fabulous potential. (Kanell,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DELTA-PILOTS _ ATLANTA _ Delta Air Lines and its pilot union are
unlikely to meet their goal of a new contract agreement by May 1,
when the current deal becomes amendable, company and union
officials agree. The two sides say the talks are progressing
reasonably well but the stickiest issue _ pay _ has yet to even hit
the table. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
