<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find items
 &HT;    By
 &HT;    Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642.
</P>
<P>
   Q: When shopping each week, I use many coupons, and my folder is
in tatters. Usually I can order one from Carole Martin gifts but
they no longer have them. I have tried to find one at the local
stores, to no avail. You are my last resort. Thank you.
</P>
<P>
   _ Carole Smith, Marietta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: We like to be the last resort. For coupons, we found two
organizers, both in plastic. The purple one from Mead Expandables
($4.99) is at CVS Pharmacy, 1610 Mount Vernon Road, Dunwoody
(770-671-2792). It measures 5 1/8 inches by 10 3/8 inches. The
other is a clear, compact Expandable Coupon File with 12 tabs that
divide each section ($5.99). It's available at the Container Store,
120 Perimeter Center West N.E. (770-351-0065) and at 3255 Peachtree
Road N.E. (404-261-4776). Or you can order at 1-800-786-7315.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for the fragrance New West Skinscent for her by
Aramis. Several stores in the area used to carry it but no longer.
I have tried other scents but they just don't seem to please me.
</P>
<P>
   _ Sandra Mallory, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Out of the West comes a fragrance _ for her _ inspired by the
mountains, desert and sunshine. This fruity-floral from Aramis
combines jonquil, marigold and hyacinth with accents of thyme,
basil and oregano and middle notes of plum, pimento and clove.
Background notes: sandalwood, patchouli, amber and tonka. We found
a 3.4-ounce bottle ($45) at Macy's Lenox Square (404-231-8910). You
can also order it through Nordstrom's beauty hotline:
1-800-723-2889.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find parchment paper for cooking and baking? I
was buying it at specialty cooking stores and sometimes at Kroger
but now I can't seem to find any brand at any store.
</P>
<P>
   _ Christine McLaughlin,
</P>
<P>
   Alpharetta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: When baking and microwaving with parchment paper, you are
helping the environment. Beyond Gourmet makes unbleached parchment
paper (a 71-square-foot roll is $6). It is available at Cook's
Warehouse, 549-1 Amsterdam Ave. N.E. (404-815-4993). No chlorine is
used in the making of this product, says the manufacturer.
Therefore, ``no harmful byproducts are released into our
environment.''
</P>
<P>
   In baking, you can use parchment paper to line baking sheets and
cake pans to prevent scorching. No need to grease, either. Also,
tightly wrap the paper around fish or veggies for oven poaching.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for McCann's Quick Cooking Microwave Oatmeal. It
came in one big bag and you could scoop it out.
</P>
<P>
   _ Marcia Duffy, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Soon you will be starting the day with a healthful bowl of
McCann's Quick Cooking Irish Oatmeal, a microwave product. All you
do is add milk or water and zap in the microwave for 1-2 minutes.
It's available in a 1-pound box for $2.49 at most Harry's in a
Hurry and Harry's Farmers Market stores, including the one at 1180
Upper Hembree Road, Roswell (770-664-6300). ``This is a natural
product,'' says the manufacturer, ``made from the whole grain of
Irish oats. Oatmeal is an excellent source of fiber, contains no
salt or cholesterol and is naturally low in fat.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find Sprayway ammonia-free glass cleaner, which
is the best glass cleaner that I have ever used! The last place I
had purchased it was Costco on Peachtree Dunwoody Road. But they no
longer have it. The product is made by Sprayway Inc. in Addison,
Ill.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jan McGeough, Dunwoody, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Spray away! We found your cleaner at Action Glass &AMP; Mirror,
890 Avon Ave. S.W. (404-753-0810). A 19-ounce can is $3.25. The
company will also ship orders. In addition to making glass shine,
Sprayway can also be used on chrome, tile and porcelain.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
</P>
<P>
   Marylin Johnson writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
