FIFE (Phoenix) - Former Gov. Fife Symington will take the witness
stand Thursday in U.S. Bankruptcy Court, the first time he has
testified under oath since his 1997 criminal bank-fraud trial. He
will face his toughest questioner ever in pension-fund attorney
Michael Manning. This is expected to be the climatic action in
Symington's attempt to get out from under $18 million in debt. By
JERRY KAMMER. Story will move in the `A` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
STUMP (Washington) - Rep. Bob Stump, who likes blue jeans and plain
talk, sent out formal invitations announcing his moment of
immortality: The unveiling of his portrait for the Capitol. As a
committee chairman (Veterans Affairs), he is entitled to one at
taxpayer expense. He joins a small list of Arizonans accorded this
honor, including Barry Goldwater. By JEFF BARKER. Story will move
in the `A` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
BOY (Undated) - Unlike Elian Gonzalez, a little boy from Guatemala
- David Juan Sebastian - sits trapped in a detention center in
Coolidge. Unlike Elian, the Guatemalan boy - like so many who enter
the U.S. illegally - has virtually no chance of remaining in this
country. While Elian is being afforded every possible consideration
to remain in the United States, the reality for thousands of
unaccompanied minors is they are either immediately deported or
kept in detention centers. By DANIAL GONZALEZ. Story will move in
the `A` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
