gangs, hate and violence in the wake of continuing news about the
White supremacist Devil Dogs. This one is expected to generate more
public outrage against town and school officials' practice of
denying the size and seriousness of the gang. By EDYTHE JENSEN.
Story will move in the `A` category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) - Thursday, as she buries her daughter,
Vicki Fernandez wants to know if there has been a more important
story reported recently in `The Arizona Republic`c or any
newspaper, than one involving the tragic death of a loving mother
who did nothing but work hard and care for her boys. So I tell her:
No. By EJ MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
categories. &QL;
</P>
