<HEADER>
A1393 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e BC-WRESTLING-KOWALSKI     03-29 0307
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-KOWALSKI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    WRESTLING GRAPEVINE
 &HT;    EDS. With WRESTLING-TAGTEAM, WRESTLING-KOWALSKI
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   It may be the biggest pay-per-view event in history when the WWF
presents an unprecidented 12 hours of programming this weekend.
Fans can order an ``all-day'' coverage package for $49.95 or just
the match coverage for $34.95. The ``all-day'' coverage includes:
``WrestleMania 2000'' matches, highlights of the best matches from
``WrestleManias I-XV,'' interviews with some of the WWF superstars
from the past and present, exclusive backstage access to
``WrestleMania 2000,'' features from WWF Axxess: The Fan Festival
from the Anaheim Convention Center, and exlcusive post-show
interviews with some of the winners and losers.
</P>
<P>
   With Bill Busch's resignation last week, the WCW is searching
for a new leader again. Although he will be working with Vince
Russo in the creative end of the show, Eric Bischoff is not
considered a candidate for the executive vice president position by
Time Warner, the parent company that runs WCW. Some people feel
that if WCW can turn things around in the next couple of months,
Time Warner may change its mind.
</P>
<P>
   For those of you who have seen the documentary ``Beyond the
Mat,'' there was a pleasant surprise at Monday's ``Nitro'' show.
Independent wrestler Mike Modesti, who has a tryout with the WWF in
the movie, earned an impressive first victory for WCW and appears
to have a bright future with the organization.
</P>
<P>
   Looks as though WCW spared no expense in making their movie,
``Ready to Rumble,'' which will be in theaters nationwide next
weekend. David Arquette, Scott Caan and Oliver Platt star along
with WCW wrestlers Diamond Dallas Page and Sting.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
