</P>
<P>
   With the outbreak of World War II, Powell enlisted with the
Welch Regiment, in which his father had served. He spent two years
as an infantry 2nd lieutenant before transferring to the
Intelligence Corps, with which he served in London until 1945.
</P>
<P>
   After the war, Powell resumed work on ``John Aubrey and His
