   Powell was named a commander of the order of the British Empire
in 1956 but refused a knighthood in 1973. A knight, he wrote in his
journal, was ``rather an awful thing to be.'' He was happy to be
made a companion of honor in 1988, however. ``Rather cheered,'' he
wrote in his journal, ``as CH eminently respectable order (65
members), which most people have never heard of. Those who have
know its standing.''
</P>
