<P>
   NY-GIULIANI-POLICE (New York) _ Even at a time when he is
defending his police force daily from what he has described as
``bashers,'' Mayor Rudolph Giuliani is facing increasingly vocal
criticism of his style and tactics on law enforcement matters from
an unlikely quarter: police officers. Although many appreciate his
support for the officers involved in the recent police shooting of
an unarmed black man, many also say that Giuliani's zero tolerance
approach to crime, his limited outreach to the black and Latino
communities and his criticism of the dead man, have needlessly
deepened the divisions between the police force and many
communities. By Laurie Flynn.
