resonate strongly within the national debate over the place of gay
men and lesbians in religious organizations, the rabbis of
Judaism's Reform branch on Wednesday declared that gay
relationships are ``worthy of affirmation'' through Jewish ritual,
and that Reform rabbis who officiate at same-sex ceremonies will
have the support of the branch's rabbinic body _ as will those who
do not. By Gustav Niebuhr.
</P>
<P>
   GUNS-SMITH (Undated) _ Smith &AMP; Wesson, the nation's oldest and
largest handgun maker, is struggling with industry opposition to
its agreement to restrictions on the way it makes and distributes
its handguns. The company agreed on March 17 to a wide array of
restrictions in exchange for ending many of the 30 lawsuits filed
against it by cities and counties across the nation. By Fox
Butterfield and Raymond Hernandez.
