</P>
<P>
   Reefer: JUDIASM-SAMESEX-UNION (Greensboro, N.C.) _ The rabbis of
Judaism's Reform movement declare that gay relationships are
``worthy of affirmation'' through Jewish ritual, and that Reform
rabbis who decide to officiate at same-sex ceremonies will have the
support of the branch's rabbinic body _ as will those who decide
they will not. By Gustav Niebuhr. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m.
ET in ``a'' news file.) 1,200 words.
</P>
<P>
   NY-GIULIANI-POLICE (New York) _ Mayor Rudolph Giuliani is facing
increasingly vocal criticism of his style and tactics on law
enforcement matters from an unlikely quarter: police officers.
Although many appreciate his support for the officers involved in
the recent police shooting of an unarmed black man, many also say
that Giuliani's zero tolerance approach to crime, his limited
outreach to the black and Latino communities and his criticism of
the dead man, have needlessly deepened the divisions between the
police force and many communities. By Laurie Flynn. (Scheduled to
move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Reefer: OPEC (Vienna, Austria) _ Just hours after Iran angrily
broke ranks with other OPEC members, its leaders sent oil prices
down by announcing here that they would, after all, attempt to
raise production in line with the rest of the oil producing
nations. By Edmund L. Andrews. (The story has moved in ``f'' news
file; it will be updated.)
</P>
