withdrawal from south Lebanon later this year, the South Lebanon
Army. a 3,000-man force of Lebanese Muslims, Christians and Druze
long allied with Israel, worries about its future. By John F.
Burns. (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
2,000 words.
