<SLUG> BC-TORNADO-SURVIVOR-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NO ROOF, NO WALL, BUT STILL ALIVE
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies TORNADO-TEXAS) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CHARLOTTE HUFF 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ As paramedics lifted him into the ambulance,
David Johnson looked back at the house in which he has lived for
more than 30 years.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know the roof is off,'' said the 70-year-old man, whose
house stood near Montgomery Ward west of downtown Fort Worth. ``And
the east wall of the house was gone.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnson, who suffered a gashed stomach, was buried under debris
in his damaged house.
</P>
<P>
   Wednesday, he was within hours of being discharged from Harris
Methodist Fort Worth, and was trying to decide what to do next.
</P>
<P>
   He owns the two-bedroom house on Mercedes Avenue and has
insurance.
</P>
<P>
   ``Thank God,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   But his finances depend on Social Security. The only possessions
he's sure he still has are in one plastic bag: the clothes he wore
to the hospital.
</P>
<P>
   He left the house without his glasses. Hospital staff members
have been helping him look up phone numbers as he calls his
insurance company and tracks down a place to live temporarily.
</P>
<P>
   Mostly, he talks about how the wind swept out of nowhere. He was
doing yardwork with his roommate, Gregory Bufano, when the debris
started flying.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was trying to get back into the house to get into the
bathtub, because I have a cast-iron bathtub,'' Johnson said. ``I
was hugging the back wall of the house to get back into the
house.''
</P>
<P>
   Bufano, who still had dried blood on his ear Wednesday, helped
rescue Johnson and load him into the ambulance. But he lost track
of where Johnson had gone, until Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's like a grandfather to me,'' Bufano said.
</P>
<P>
   (Staff writer Mike Lee contributed to this report. Visit the
Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
