<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-PARADOX-REVIEW-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
`PARADOX' FOUND WHERE LEAST EXPECTED
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: Fact box below; ``tonight'' refers to Thurs., Mar. 30) 
Our rating: 2{ stars 
By DAVID KRONKE 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Writer/journalist Holly Morris has hit upon a revelation: Take a
camera crew with you on your vacation, and even if no one knows who
you are, you'll get preferential treatment and access to folks who
otherwise wouldn't give you the time of day.
</P>
<P>
   In ``Adventure Divas Cuba: Paradox Found,'' Morris wanders
peripatetically around the land of Castro and hooks up with a
female hip-hop trio, a filmmaker, a feminist broadcaster, an exiled
Black Panther, an author of erotic poetry and a Santeria priestess.
The idea is to locate and ascertain the perspectives of women of
substance in foreign locales, but even Morris tires of her goal at
points, running off to go fishing for a day, playing with her
favorite tchotchke that she brought from home, or just grousing
that she feels ``cranky.''
</P>
<P>
   She says things like, ``The sensual is a food group here,'' and,
of men ogling women, observes, ``Somehow it lacks the icky feeling
it has at home,'' a statement that seems simultaneously naive and
condescending. Nonetheless, she's a predominantly winning tour
guide, though her ``you go, girl'' vibe will strike some viewers as
a little on the too-cute side.
</P>
<P>
   This special purports to be the first of a series of programs
touring exotic destinations in search of strong and colorful women.
In truth, however, it looks more like a calling card for Morris to
find a gig with one of those TV newsmagazines that are increasingly
proliferating where the emphasis is on subjectivity and the
correspondent's persona and less on substantive reporting. For
which Morris, with a keener segment producer and sterner editor at
her service, would seem a natural. &QL; 
_______ &QL; 
The show: ``'Adventure Divas Cuba: Paradox Found.'' &QL; 
What: Travelogue with a feminist slant. &QL; 
The stars: Holly Morris hosts. &QL; 
Where: PBS. &QL; 
When: 8 tonight. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
