</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Archives building escapes damage
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The National Archives and Records Administration
Center in East Point, Ga., sustained no fire, smoke or water damage
from Tuesday's blaze at a neighboring pallet company, according to
James McSweeney, administrator of the regional facility.
</P>
<P>
   The facility was inspected by a local fire and water damage
restoration company, BMS Catastrophe Worldwide, and given a clean
bill of health, McSweeney said.
</P>
<P>
   L&AMP;R Pallet Inc., at 2316 Lawrence St., was destroyed. A cause of
the fire has not yet been determined, East Point Fire Battalion
Chief Daryl Smith said.
</P>
