<SLUG> BC-BKC-SCHOOP-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TWO USC GUARDS WON'T RETURN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC point guard Rashad Jones and shooting guard
Malachi Thurston will not return to the team next season, according
to sources within the basketball program.
</P>
<P>
   Jones, a 6-foot-1 junior from San Jose, has a chronically
separated shoulder that will prevent him from playing next season
and effectively ends his college career. He will continue to attend
USC on a medical-redshirt scholarship.
</P>
<P>
   Thurston, a 6-4 freshman from Oakland, has encountered academic
problems and will probably be forced to enroll at a junior college
next year.
</P>
<P>
   Jones averaged 0.9 points and 1.0 rebounds last season. Thurston
averaged 1.6 points and 1.0 rebounds. Neither played a key role for
the Trojans.
</P>
<P>
   The departure of Jones and Thurston means USC will have two
extra scholarships available for the spring signing period, which
begins next month. USC could sign as many as four players in April,
but it's doubtful the Trojans will sign more than two.
</P>
<P>
   Point guard Robert Hutchinson of Okaloosa-Walton Community
College in Niceville, Fla., reaffirmed his oral commitment last
weekend during a campus visit, and USC is waiting for Laguna Beach
High guard Travis Hanour to make a decision. Hanour visited Utah
last weekend but is expected to chose between USC and Arizona. He
originally committed to USC in February but is currently undecided.
</P>
<P>
   USC coach Henry Bibby has been out of town recruiting and was
unavailable for comment. Bibby recently visited Puerto Rico, where
he scouted 6-5 guard Roberto Nieves. But Nieves is unlikely to
attend USC, because he has not met the necessary academic
requirements.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-29-00 2155EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT20000329.0383 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-29 21:56 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
