   (NYT40) UNDATED -- March 29, 2000 -- NY-CHINESE-SCULPTURE --
Customs officials moved Wednesday to seize a 10th-century marble
sculpture that they said had been stolen from an ancient Chinese
tomb and was about to be sold at Christie's auction gallery. The
sculpture, a painted relief panel, is believed to be 1 of 10 that
were taken by raiders who blasted their way into the Five Dynasties
tomb of Wang Chuzhi in Hebeicq Province, in northeastern China, in
1994. (United States Customs Service/The New York Times)
