Julia Harrison, 79, was first elected to represent Flushing on the
City Council in 1979. But next year, the city's 1996 term limits
law will force her out of office, along with 35 others on the
51-member City Council. And the race for her seat is being seen as
a kind of weather vane of political power of Asian-Americans in New
York, where none have ever held citywide office. Candidates for the
council from Flushing include, from left, Terence Y. Park, Ethel T.
