Digging a hole can be hard work, but the job can be made easier if
you have the right tools. Before breaking ground, call your local
utility companies and outline your plans. Have them come to the
site and locate and mark any underground water, gas, electrical and
drainage lines, and telephone and television cables. Cutting into
one of these can disrupt service and possibly injure or kill you.
These line markings are only approximate, so to be on the safe
side, avoid digging within two feet of them. (Edward R.
Lipinski/The New York Times) LITE
