   (NYT26) UNDATED -- March 29, 2000 -- CIR-VOICE-RECOGNITION-2 --
Some tips for improving accuracy with speech-recognition software:
When you do the initial training, don't be on your best behavior
voice-wise, or else the software will expect that from you all the
time; Pronounce each word distinctly, and let your mouth and lips
actually move; Position the microphone properly and consistently at
the side of the mouth and slightly below, a thumb's width to two
fingers away, to avoid recognition of breath sounds. (Tony
Cenicola/The New York Times)
</P>
