u s BC-NCAA-AGENT-NYT     03-29 0191
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NCAA-AGENT-NYT </SLUG>
 
Undated: NBA salary.
<TEXT>
<P>
   One of the allegations in Fleisher's lawsuit, filed in New York
State Supreme Court in Manhattan, was that Miller lured away
Fleisher's clients with promises of ``romantic liaisons'' with
unnamed Wilhelmina supermodels.
</P>
<P>
   According to documents obtained by The New York Times, Miller
sent a faxed letter to Thomas LaVilla, an outside consultant for
Wilhelmina, from the Assist Sports Management office on June 10,
1998. After initial pleasantries, the letter reads: ``Kevin Garnett
has a crush on a young black model who was recently seen on a
L'Oreal television campaign. Do you have any thoughts on this
matter. Let me know. Best regards, Andy.''
</P>
<P>
   LaVilla responded the same day with a letter that read in part:
``Andy, attached please find Kevin's new girlfriends. We will be
getting back to you on the particulars. If he likes one _ just give
me a call. Best regards _ Tommy.''
</P>
<P>
   Gord Esch, the owner of Wilhelmina models, said recently he
thought the letters were a joke. ``Using these letters to get
publicity for a lawsuit, dragging Wilhelmina into this, is just
absurd,'' Esch said.
</P>
</TEXT>
